Cummins to Rizwan, no run some seam movement straight away, nipping in to hit Rizwan on the thigh

Cummins to Rizwan, OUT past the edge! Or has he got him? Australia appeal, Cummins is convinced, and likewise convinces Finch to take a review when the umpire says no. Kumar Dharmasena is the third umpire, and he notes a sound as ball passes bat. And ultra edge shows a

Behrendorff to Imam-ul-Haq, 2 runs too straight, and he's milked in front of square on the leg side for a brace
Behrendorff to Imam-ul-Haq, no run full and seaming away outside off. Imam steps into a watchful leave

Behrendorff to Imam-ul-Haq, no run Behrendorff hits a length, on off stump, and Imam defends to cover
Behrendorff to Imam-ul-Haq, no run just short of a good length, but nicely straight and Imam is a little cramped for room as he defends

And that's all from your commentary team, Andrew McGlashan and Liam Brickhill. Australia will go to the fourth ODI in Dubai on Friday with the series in the bag. Pakistan have two more chances to get it right. Until next time, goodbye!
Pat Cummins is the Player of the Match

Australia won by 80 runs
Player of the match is Pat Cummins, AUS
